beast-splitter (3.0.2) stable; urgency=medium

  * Release for PiAware 3.0.2
  * Portability fixes for newer libstdc++ versions
  * Work around some (misbuilt?) Boost versions that don't support hardware
    flow control

 -- Oliver Jowett <oliver@mutability.co.uk>  Wed, 27 Jul 2016 17:32:20 +0100

beast-splitter (3.0.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Release to github
  * Add support for network input
  * Improved logging about setting changes
  * Drop hotplug support (it's a bit fragile), require explicit configuration
  * Don't wait for a full 512-byte buffer before processing input commands
  * When emulating GPS timestamps from 12MHz, set the emulation bit in status
    messages

 -- Oliver Jowett <oliver@mutability.co.uk>  Fri, 15 Jul 2016 13:58:56 +0100

